<br>
That's about 20pp per skill increase. Skill-ups were pretty quick with at most eight attempts between skill-ups and I had one run of five skill-ups in a row.  I bought all the ingredients and all the vials and suspensions --- I am not patient enough to make my own vials, although sealed vials ~were~ costing me about 7pp each, I think, and finished poisons selling back for ~6pp.<br>
<br>
I've got around 105 practice points at level 58 but I'm pretty sure that the cost to raise Make Poison by using practice points would be higher than the cost to just make poisons. If, however, Spirit of Sloth actually is a break-even proposition, it might be more economical to get my skill up to the point I can make SoS. /shrug  Depends on how things go once I finish Calcium Rot and move on to the Kaladim poisons.<br>
<br>
I've been hoarding practice points for so long because (like charged items) I'm never sure when I'm gonna need them and it's impossible to get more, later (well, I've got 10 more coming to me from 59th and 60th at least). Not much ELSE to spend them on now, though. I -did- bump Dodge up six points in level 58 but otherwise most skills max quickly enough.<br>
